| Canada's Wayne Crookes Sues the Net                                |
|   from the shotgun-doesn't-begin-to-cover-it dept.                 |
|   posted by kdawson on Sunday April 22, @08:12 (Censorship)        |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/22/0148255          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]newtley writes "Wayne Crookes, the Green Party of Canada's
ex-financier, is in effect trying to sue the Internet. He's going after
the Wikipedia, Google, and [1]openpolitics.ca (run up by federal Green
Party activist Michael Pilling) claiming he's suffered, '[2]an immense
amount of frustration and emotional distress' over postings. Some 15
others may also have been targeted. "Mr. Crookes seems to be [3]'trying
to unwrite history,' Pilling says. 'He was a central figure in the growth
of the Green Party. His actions were highly controversial and if we have
freedom of speech in this country, people should be allowed to talk about
them.'" Newtley adds in a posting submitted 121 minutes later: "Literally
15 minutes after I posted [the foregoing], there was a knock on my door.
It was a writ server telling me I, too, have been [4]named in a lawsuit
launched by Wayne Crookes..."

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/22/0148255

