| Is Your GPS Naive?                                                 |
|   from the what's-a-dikfor-anyway dept.                            |
|   posted by CmdrTaco on Sunday April 22, @13:41 (Hardware Hacking) |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/22/1452247     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]mi writes "Many GPS devices today will try to scan the FM bands for
traffic advisories in the area to display on their screens. The signals,
however, are neither authenticated nor encrypted, and one can — with
commonly available electronics — construct a device to [1]broadcast bogus
advisories. Possible codes range from "bullfight ahead" to "terrorist
attack"..."

