| The Germs' Drummer Arrested For Carrying Soap                      |
|   from the keeping-his-nose-clean dept.                            |
|   posted by kdawson on Sunday April 22, @15:50 (It's funny.  Laugh.|
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/22/195244            |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]dwrugh writes "The drummer for the seminal punk band The Germs, Don
Bolles, was arrested in Orange County because a [1]field-test kit
indicated his bottle of Dr. Bronner's soap contained GHB, the date-rape
drug. (Here is an [2]interview with Bolles.) Using the same test kit,
available on the web for $20 for a pack of 10, according to Bolles'
attorney on NBC this morning, other soaps tested positive for GHB. But of
course since it's just soap, when you test it in a real crime lab it
comes back negative. Makes you wonder what other common household
products also test positive, and how many others have been arrested based
on faulty test kits who didn't have the resources to defend themselves."

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/22/195244

